# Optilibria - AI Assistant Rules

## Project Context
- **Project**: Optilibria - Quantum Annealing Problem Solver
- **Organization**: AlaweinLabs
- **Repository**: https://github.com/AlaweinLabs/Optilibria
- **Language**: Python
- **Framework**: Scientific Computing, Optimization

## Code Style
- Follow PEP 8 for Python code
- Use type hints for all function signatures
- Write docstrings in NumPy style
- Maximum line length: 100 characters
- Use meaningful variable names

## Testing
- Write pytest tests for all new features
- Maintain >80% code coverage
- Include doctest examples in docstrings
- Run tests before committing

## Documentation
- Update README.md for new features
- Document all public APIs
- Include usage examples
- Keep CHANGELOG.md updated

## Git Workflow
- Use conventional commits (feat:, fix:, docs:, etc.)
- Reference issues in commit messages
- Keep commits atomic and focused
- Write descriptive commit messages

## Dependencies
- Use pyproject.toml for dependency management
- Pin major versions, allow minor updates
- Document why each dependency is needed
- Keep dependencies minimal

## Organization Standards
- This project is part of AlaweinLabs organization
- Follow organization-wide governance policies
- Maintain consistency with other AlaweinLabs projects
- Use organization templates and standards
